Fed ' s Moskow speaks to price stability goal . Chicago Federal Reserve Bank President Michael Moskow said on Thursday that price stability will be evident when inflation does not factor in to consumer or business decisions . When Moskow was asked how price stability will be evident when it is reached , he replied : " When inflation does not interfere with the actions of consumers and business . " Moskow was responding to reporters ' questions following a speech delivered here . ( ( - - N . A . Treasury Desk , 212 - 859 - 1600 ) ) 
